12. **Scene**: The walls begin to *breathe*;  
13. **Scene**: A child walks in—*and sees Eli*—and says, “You’re the one who cleaned my dad’s shoes.”  
14. **Scene**: The station flickers—*and Eli feels his name being erased from his own mind*;  
15. **Scene**: He writes one last name—*his own*—and the station vanishes;  
16. **Scene**: A man on the street stops, stares at the sky, and says, “I remember a janitor.”  
17. **Scene**: A child drops a pencil—*it’s labeled “Eli”*;  
18. **Scene**: The city’s clocks all stop for exactly 13 seconds;  
19. **Scene**: A new janitor walks into the station—*and doesn’t see the door*;  
20. **Scene**: The final frame: the broom lies on the floor—*and the floor is clean*.

